laboratory_examinations.findings: Normal sinus rhythm, ST-segment elevations of 1 to 4 mm in leads V1 through V6, hyperacute T waves in leads V4, V5, and V6, and ST-segment depressions of 1 to 1.5 mm in the inferior leads.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: The ST-segment changes seen on the ECG resolved completely between episodes.

laboratory_examinations.findings: 35-mm-long segment of severe narrowing (90% stenosis) in the middle of the left anterior descending coronary artery, consistent with intramural hematoma, with distal haziness consistent with a dissection site, and minimal vascular disease in other coronary arteries.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up angiogram after 48 hours showed improved blood flow (TIMI grade 3), a shorter segment of stenosis (approximately 25 mm), and resolution of the distal dissection flap.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Nearly complete resolution of the dissection and normal left ventricular function.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Significant improvement from the initial angiogram.
